      "raw_text": "provisions, grade separation or any\nthing else.\n\n\nEarling today remained in his\ncar, clOseted with his Spokane at\ntorneys and right of way agent,\nJames Walsh. At II a. m. it was\nannounced that he would take run\nout to Spirit Lake on the Blackwell\nroad and be back here this evening.\n\n\nOne of the prominent workers in\nthe citizens committee having in\ncharge the effort to secure the pass\nage of the North Coast and Milwau-\nkee franchises by the city council\nsaid today that the committee had\nnot seen Earling and that 1t had no\noccasion to see him; that this was\na citizens fight, in which an effort\nwas being made in behalf of the in\ndustrial prosperity of the city.\nrather than for the benefit of the\nrailroads trying to secure admis-\nsion."
